7:["$","article",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-white","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12","children":[["$","header",null,{"className":"mb-8","children":[["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4","children":"Myths about ISO 45001 OHSMS Certification"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-4 text-gray-600","children":[["$","time",null,{"dateTime":"2026-01-02T06:31:41+00:00","children":"January 2, 2026"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 rounded-full text-sm","children":"general"}]]}]]}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-8 p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500","children":["$","p",null,{"className":"text-gray-700 italic","children":"Some people allegedly claim that ISO 45001 certification has several myths surrounding it and it will be arduous to distinguish those myths from reality. In"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed","children":[["$","p","0",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Myths about ISO 45001 OHSMS Certification"}],["$","p","1",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"When you implement your ISO 45001 OHSMS (Occupational Health & Safety Management System) for your organization, You may notice that ISO 45001 certification has several myths surrounding it allegedly and it will be arduous to distinguish those myths from the reality. In this article, we are going to look into the six most common myths that revolve around ISO 45001 OHSMS and take a look at to clarify what's true and what is not."}],["$","p","2",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Six Myths about ISO 45001 OHSMS standard"}],["$","p","3",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Myth #1: ISO 45001 OHSMS is standard which is applicable only to manufacturing"}],["$","p","4",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Usually, a manufacturing company could have many possibilities apparent hazards compared to other types of organization, this ISO certification is claimed to be employed by any organization in any business. The main focus of ISO 45001 certification is to comprehend the legal necessities that are applicable to your specific organization and then use this information to pinpoint what hazards you have got for your processes. There could also be risks of falls in a warehouse, knife hazards while setting up a kitchen, or tripping and shock hazards in any type of organization. By completely assessing and narrowing down your specific hazards, you will be able to rectify the danger and risk posed. Moreover, those hazards are most vital in enhancing the overall occupational health & safety management system performance of your organization."}],["$","p","5",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"Myth #2: ISO 45001 is not required for legally abiding companies"}],["$","p","6",{"className":"mb-6 text-justify leading-8","children":"The most vital part of ISO 45001 OHSMS is the legal compliance, however, ISO 45001 goes beyond just abiding by applicable laws and dealing towards the improvement of your organization OH&S performance. ISO certification standards need that you just establish the legal necessities that are applicable to your organization, determine how you will sustain to date on these necessities, to come up with a plan - what you would like to do to comply with these ISO 45001 requirements and then measure your ability to fulfil those necessities. However, ISO 45001 OHSMS concentrate more on enhancing OH&S performance which is considered as the most significant part than just meeting legal necessities."}],"$L10","$L11","$L12","$L13","$L14","$L15","$L16","$L17","$L18"]}],"$L19"]}]}]
